"meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Hywel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name. Some write the name Hoel, which they render 'lordly;' if so, it may come from huail, a vice-regent, regent. Arthur derives the surname Howell from Corn. -Brit, houl, the sun; and he adds, high, exalted.' But Hywel is rather from hywel, conspicuous."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Dda","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Jewish (from North Africa): from the male personal name <i>ʿAdda</i>, used in the Maghreb, a pet form of any of the many names beginning with <i>ʿAbd</i> ‘servant’.","Turkish: ornamental or topographic name from <i>ada</i> ‘island’.","Filipino: unexplained."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Merion","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: derived in the Roman period from Latin <i>Marianus</i> (a derivative of <b>Marius</b>; )."],"variants":[{"name":"Merrion","meanings":["Variant of   Meirion ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord Merion Blaidd ap Hywel Dda was born in 0968, in Dolbenmaen, Caernarfonshire, Wales, his father, Hywed Dda of Wales, was 19 and his mother, Lady Eleanor De Dyfed, was 15. He married Blaidd ap Hywed of Gest in 0992, in Dolbenmaen, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 0993, in Rhuddlan, Flintshire, Wales, at the age of 25."},"et":{"0968–993":"0968–0993","0968–0993":"0968–0993","0972–Female":"0972–Surnud","0993–1028":"0993–1028","0950–1008":"0950–1008","0953–1010":"0953–1010","1008":"1008","0953":"0953","992":"0992","0950":"0950","1028":"1028","0972":"0972","993":"0993","0993